fr.zelus.jarvis.core

Class OrchestrationService

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zelus.jarvis.core.OrchestrationService

  • public class OrchestrationService
extends Object
    Reads an OrchestrationModel and returns the JarvisActions associated to the provided RecognizedIntents.

    This class is used by JarvisCore to retrieve the JarvisAction to execute when a RecognizedIntent has been computed from an user input. The OrchestrationService takes care of the JarvisAction construction, and returns an valid action instances to be executed by the JarvisCore component.

    See Also:
    JarvisCore, JarvisAction, RecognizedIntent

      • getActionsFromIntent

        public List<ActionInstance> getActionsFromIntent(RecognizedIntent recognizedIntent,
                                                 JarvisSession session)
        Retrieves and instantiate the JarvisActions associated to the provided recognizedIntent.

        This class navigates the underlying OrchestrationModel and retrieves the Action associated to the provided recognizedIntent. These Actions are then reified into JarvisActions and instantiated by using the recognizedIntent's values.

        Parameters:
        recognizedIntent - the RecognizedIntent to retrieve the JarvisActions from
        Returns:
        a List containing the instantiated JarvisActions associated to the provided recognizedIntent.
        See Also:
        JarvisModuleRegistry.getJarvisModule(String), JarvisModule.createJarvisAction(ActionInstance, RecognizedIntent, fr.zelus.jarvis.core.session.JarvisSession)
